# ADDENDUM: non-ADK-user runtime impact audit (2026-06-10)

User asked to verify the integration has no runtime impact on weave users
who do not use ADK. Findings (no fixes needed — design is fully lazy):

- Registration (instrumentGoogleADK at import weave): two in-memory Map
  pushes in instrumentations.ts. No I/O, no module resolution, no semver
  eval. NODE_DEBUG=module on the built dist shows ZERO '@google/adk'
  lookups during import (the only 'adk' matches are weave's own
  googleAdk.js file loading).
- CJS hot path: Module.prototype.require patch is PRE-EXISTING weave core
  (utils/commonJSLoader.ts); per-require cost is one O(1) Map.has on
  '<name>@<subPath>'. The expensive branch (requirePackageJson + semifies +
  hook) runs only when '@google/adk@dist/cjs/index.js' is actually required.
- ESM: only for hosts that opt into --import=weave/instrument; adds one
  import-in-the-middle Hook(['@google/adk']) — parity with the existing 5
  integrations.
- Import-time A/B (12 runs each, dist built at stack merge-base 0b0ea6e1a9
  vs stack top): median 115.3ms vs 105.9ms, mins 90.6 vs 90.0 — delta below
  noise.
- Process listeners after import: beforeExit 0 / exit 0, identical to base.
  registerBeforeExitHookOnce only fires on the first traced ADK invocation.
- genai constructor check (isAdkInternalClientOptions): runs only for
  @google/genai users, O(#headers) per client construction; non-ADK clients
  keep being wrapped identically (51 genai tests green).
- Dependencies: runtime "dependencies" unchanged; @google/adk + lodash are
  devDependencies; the lodash-es->lodash mapping is jest-only.
- No-ADK e2e: hostApps fixtures install the packed SDK into hosts WITHOUT
  @google/adk and pass (cjs-basic + esm-basic, run in the full suite).

Bench method: git worktree --detach at merge-base in /tmp, symlinked
node_modules, npm run build both sides, 12x require() timing each.
